From: Matthew Feickert <matthew.feickert@cern.ch>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 04:02:48 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] Manual: fix stray 'R' before @end verbatim in Starting.texi

A stray 'R' character on line 469 of Manual/Starting.texi prevented
newer versions of texinfo (e.g. as shipped in conda-forge's alma9
build image) from recognising the closing '@end verbatim' tag, which
caused the makeinfo invocation that produces Sherpa.info to fail with
'no matching @end verbatim' / 'no matching @end smallformat' errors.

The texinfo manual specifies that '@end verbatim' must appear on a
line by itself (preceded only by optional whitespace). Older texinfo
releases tolerated additional leading text, but recent releases
enforce the rule strictly.
---
 Manual/Starting.texi | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Manual/Starting.texi b/Manual/Starting.texi
index 9211f94..b108e37 100644
--- a/Manual/Starting.texi
+++ b/Manual/Starting.texi
@@ -466,7 +466,7 @@ Initialized the Fragmentation_Handler.
 Initialized the Soft_Photon_Handler.
 Hadron_Decay_Map::Read:   Initializing HadronDecays.dat. This may take some time.
 Initialized the Hadron_Decay_Handler, Decay model = Hadrons
-R@end verbatim
+@end verbatim
 @end smallformat
 
 Then Sherpa will start to integrate the cross sections. The output will look 
-- 
